fix(critical): prevent duplicate Stripe subscriptions per customer

Root cause: every visit to /trial called create-trial-subscription, which
only short-circuited if existing sub was already trialing/active. Any other
state (incomplete being the common case) caused a brand new Stripe
subscription to be created on the same customer. Old subs were never
cancelled - they stayed attached and silently activated/billed whenever the
customer eventually added a payment method, producing repeated charges
(4x in 24h on louiz@fluxberlin.com).

Fix in app/api/onboarding.py create_trial_subscription:
- Before creating, list ALL Stripe subs for the customer.
- If any is trialing/active/past_due, short-circuit, never create another.
- If any is incomplete, REUSE its pending_setup_intent instead of orphaning.
- Cancel every other orphan incomplete sub to prevent future bills.

Also: scripts/cleanup_duplicate_subs.py - one-shot remediation that scans
every Stripe customer, keeps the oldest live sub per customer, cancels the
duplicates, and refunds any invoice paid on a duplicate in the last 72h.
Run with --apply to actually execute.
